properties.areaDesc: San Juan County; Admiralty Inlet Area; Western Whatcom County; Western Skagit County
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 25 at 2:45PM PST until January 26 at 11:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds rising overnight to 20 to 30 mph with
gusts 40 to 50 mph possible. Wind shifting to southwest by
about mid morning on Sunday.

* WHERE...Western Whatcom County, Western Skagit County,
Admiralty Inlet Area and San Juan County.

* WHEN...From 3 AM to 11 AM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A low pressure center will track through
the coastal waters and reach Vancouver Island around daybreak.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 11 AM PST SUNDAY
